129
00:07:02,501 --> 00:07:03,696
Scott: Well, the reason I liked the MX1000.

130
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:04,940
Rym: No, it wasn't even tribes.

131
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:05,760
Rym: It was like Counter-Strike.

132
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:12,260
Scott: The reason I like the MX1000 is first of all, you can just charge it in a cradle instead of batteries, which is nice.

133
00:07:12,461 --> 00:07:13,020
Rym: I hate batteries.

134
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:14,600
Rym: At least I don't like batteries.

135
00:07:14,620 --> 00:07:16,940
Scott: If I'm going to get a wireless mouse, it better not have batteries.

136
00:07:17,060 --> 00:07:20,500
Scott: Well, actually the wireless mouse that goes to my laptop has batteries, but that's obvious.

137
00:07:20,660 --> 00:07:21,160
Scott: That's different.

138
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:21,780
Scott: That's different.

139
00:07:22,981 --> 00:07:30,100
Scott: Two, you can move the scroll wheel left and right for some horizontal scrolling action, which you can actually get used to.

140
00:07:30,181 --> 00:07:30,777
Scott: It's pretty nice.

141
00:07:31,641 --> 00:07:37,700
Scott: Third, it has these extra buttons on it, but the extra buttons aren't clumsy and they actually click solidly.

142
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:42,700
Scott: And when I'm playing an FPS, I can actually get a lot of extra functionality out of them.

143
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:47,300
Scott: And some of them are, you know, I can push some of them simultaneous with other buttons.

144
00:07:47,701 --> 00:07:51,620
Scott: So like I can use, you know, a button on the keyboard to say jump.

145
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:53,480
Scott: Normally I can move that to the mouse.

146
00:07:53,841 --> 00:08:01,980
Scott: And now I've got an extra keyboard button within reach and I can do a lot more FPS controlling with moving my hand around the keyboard a lot less.

147
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:04,679
Scott: I keep my hand in the same spot and I can do a lot more things.

148
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:09,319
Rym: See, now I think this might be why we have different tastes in mice and why I don't need the extra buttons.

149
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:17,099
Rym: The way I set my hands on the keyboard, I have never in all the FPS I've ever played, not had a key ready to go.

150
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:20,280
Rym: And I actually, I can do all the things I need to do simultaneously as it is.

151
00:08:20,660 --> 00:08:31,200
Scott: So in some FPS is, you know, I can do that even if I have, you know, a one button mouse because I just need the one button to shoot and I've got buttons for everything else, you know, on the keyboard.

152
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:35,580
Scott: But some FPSs are really complicated and sometimes I want buttons to do crazy things.

153
00:08:36,059 --> 00:08:40,679
Scott: And sometimes it's not an option without extra buttons on the mouse or moving my hand around.

154
00:08:41,562 --> 00:08:44,940
Scott: Like FPS, especially FPS with inventories with full of items.

155
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:48,420
Rym: Yeah, but even then I think part of that is that you put your hand over by the arrow keys.

156
00:08:48,580 --> 00:08:49,699
Scott: No, I put it by the WASD.

157
00:08:50,622 --> 00:08:51,157
Rym: Oh, the WASD.

158
00:08:51,563 --> 00:08:52,659
Rym: But there's plenty of buttons there.

159
00:08:53,002 --> 00:08:53,658
Rym: What's wrong with you?

160
00:08:54,123 --> 00:08:54,878
Scott: I need more buttons.

161
00:08:55,124 --> 00:08:55,840
Rym: There's plenty of buttons.

162
00:08:55,980 --> 00:08:56,780
Rym: I've never run out of buttons.

163
00:08:56,900 --> 00:09:05,680
Scott: The other thing is that a lot of the buttons I would like to use are, you know, too far away from the WASD or they screw up because gaming is in Windows.

164
00:09:05,940 --> 00:09:08,879
Scott: Like the window key fucks everything up and the alt key fucks everything up.

165
00:09:09,302 --> 00:09:09,779
Rym: Alt doesn't.

166
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,359
Rym: I don't have any problems with that.

167
00:09:11,525 --> 00:09:11,717
Scott: I do.

168
00:09:12,060 --> 00:09:13,338
Scott: I have problems pushing alt in.

169
00:09:14,042 --> 00:09:15,380
Rym: I use alt to duck.

170
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:19,000
Rym: I've used alt to duck for as long as there's been ducking in FPSs.

171
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:23,300
Scott: I use a lot more keyboard shortcuts than you and a lot of them are global keyboard shortcuts.

172
00:09:23,743 --> 00:09:26,158
Scott: So I can't use those buttons in FPSs.

