Scott: I use Launchy in Windows.

177
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:32,270
Rym: Yeah?

178
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:36,280
Scott: Yeah, so I can't push like alt and space at the same time and stuff like that.

179
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:38,319
Scott: And you'd be surprised that actually comes up.

180
00:09:39,201 --> 00:09:39,577
Rym: You know what?

181
00:09:39,821 --> 00:09:41,680
Rym: I don't have Launchy on my PC at home.

182
00:09:41,740 --> 00:09:45,879
Rym: I only have it on the PC at work because I only boot into Windows to play FPSs.

183
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,080
Rym: I never run anything but Steam.

184
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,456
Scott: I use Launchy to launch my FPSs.

185
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:51,140
Rym: But I just, Steam starts when I boot.

186
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:53,060
Rym: Basically, Windows is not Windows.

187
00:09:53,202 --> 00:09:54,319
Rym: Windows is just Steam.

188
00:09:54,540 --> 00:09:55,639
Rym: When I boot, Steam starts.

189
00:09:56,281 --> 00:09:56,616
Rym: And that's it.

190
00:09:57,041 --> 00:09:58,940
Scott: Even so, I need lots of buttons.

191
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,219
Scott: Especially, like if I'm playing Tribes 2, I need lots of buttons.

192
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:03,580
Scott: And I like to put some buttons on the mouse.

